Short:        crc.library 2.0 - checksum and digest library for Amiga
Author:       toolkit@amigazen.com (amigazen project)
Uploader:     toolkit@amigazen.com (amigazen project)
Type:         util/libs
Version:      2.0
Architecture: m68k-amigaos


crc.library 2.0
===============

crc.library is a shared library for classic Amiga from amigazen project.
It provides CRC, checksum, sum, XOR, and message-digest routines used by
archivers, filesystem tools, and version-control clients.

Full source code is available at:

  https://github.com/amigazen/crc/

crc.library from amigazen project also available at:

  http://www.amigazen.com/toolkit/

amigazen project uses modern development practices to maintain and
rerelease classic Amiga open-source software.

The original crc.library author (Jim Sunrise) and GetCRC author (Dirk
Stoecker) are not affiliated with amigazen; terms are in LICENSE.md in
the source distribution.


READ THIS FIRST
---------------

 o LVOs 1-28 are binary-compatible with Jim Sunrise's crc.library v1.0
   (October 2006). Existing binaries can still OpenLibrary("crc.library", 1).

 o New functions in 2.0 are include SHA-1/SHA-256, POSIX sums, and streaming

 o md5sum was renamed DoMD5Sum at the same LVO offset (-192). The legacy
   name is available as a macro in libraries/crc.h for source compatibility.


WHAT crc.library IS FOR
-----------------------

Programs that need to verify data integrity or identify archive formats
without embedding their own table-driven checksum code:

 o Archivers and unpackers (Zip/GZip CRC-32, Arc/LhA CRC-16, BZip2, Ace)

 o File managers verifying on-disk structures

 o Git and Subversion clients (SHA-1, SHA-256, MD5)

 o Any tool that needs BSD sum, SYSV sum, or POSIX cksum


NEW IN crc.library 2.0
----------------------

 o Incremental (streaming) API for data larger than available RAM:
   CRCNew, CRCReset, CRCUpdate, CRCFinal, CRCDispose, CRCDigestLength
   Streamed output is bit-identical to the matching one-shot Do* call

 o 33 CRC_* algorithm selectors in libraries/crc.h (one per algorithm)

 o Message digests useful for version control programs:
   DoSHA1 (git object hashing), DoSHA256, DoMD5Sum (Subversion deltas)

 o POSIX / Unix checksums from GetCRC 1.19:
   DoCHS16_2 (BSD sum), DoCHS16_3 (SYSV sum), DoCRC32_7 (POSIX cksum)

 o Lazy exec memory pool for streaming contexts; CRCNew/CRCDispose are
   semaphore-protected; per-handle CRCUpdate needs no locking

 o Four reserved LVO slots before the streaming block for future growth

 o Expanded autodocs (SDK/Autodocs/crc.doc)


ONE-SHOT ALGORITHMS (v1.0 + v2.0)
---------------------------------

CRC-32 variants:  DoCRC32_1 .. DoCRC32_7
CRC-16 variants:  DoCRC16_1 .. DoCRC16_4
Checksums:        DoCHS32_1M, DoCHS32_1I, DoCHS32_2, DoCHS16_1,
                  DoCHS16_2, DoCHS16_3
XOR reduction:    DoEORB, DoEORWM, DoEORWI, DoEORLM, DoEORLI
Sums:             DoSumSB, DoSumSWM, DoSumSWI, DoSumUB, DoSumUWM,
                  DoSumUWI, DoSumLM, DoSumLI
Digests:          DoMD5Sum, DoSHA1, DoSHA256


STREAMING EXAMPLE
-----------------

  APTR h = CRCNew(CRC_SHA256);
  while ((len = Read(fh, buf, sizeof buf)) > 0)
      CRCUpdate(h, buf, len);
  CRCFinal(h, digest);
  CRCDispose(h);

